  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Can I apply for internet banking in Andhra bank without visiting the branch?",
  "response": "Yes, in most cases, you can apply for internet banking in Andhra Bank (now merged into Union Bank of India) without visiting the branch, provided you already have an active account with the bank. Here\u2019s how you can proceed:\n\n### **Steps to Apply for Internet Banking Without Visiting the Branch:**\n\n1. **Via Mobile App:**\n   - Download the Union Bank of India mobile app (or the Andhra Bank app if still available).\n   - Log in using your credentials (if you already have net banking access).\n   - Look for the option to register for internet banking or activate mobile banking.\n   - Follow the instructions to complete the registration.\n\n2. **Online Registration:**\n   - Visit the official Union Bank of India (or Andhra Bank) website.\n   - Look for the \"Internet Banking\" or \"Retail Internet Banking\" section.\n   - Click on \"New User Activation\" or \"Register Here.\"\n   - Enter your account number, CIF number, and other required details.\n   - Complete the registration process by verifying your identity through OTP (sent to your registered mobile number).\n\n3. **Customer Support:**\n   - If you face any issues, you can contact the bank's customer care or helpline.\n   - They may guide you through the process or assist in activating internet banking remotely.\n\n### **Requirements:**\n   - Active bank account with Andhra Bank (now Union Bank of India).\n   - Registered mobile number linked to your account.\n   - Debit card details (for verification purposes in some cases).\n\n### **Post-Registration:**\n   - Once registered, you\u2019ll receive login credentials (User ID and password) via SMS or email.\n   - Use these credentials to log in to the internet banking portal or app.\n\nIf you face any issues or the above methods don\u2019t work, you may need to visit the branch or submit a request through the bank\u2019s support channels.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
